-- Wall Street gains on Italian reform
-- 
-- Fri Nov 11, 2011 4:39pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/11/11/us-markets-stocks-idUSTRE7AA3VY20111111

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Stocks jumped on Friday, ending higher on the week after the Italian Senate's approval of economic reforms gave some relief to worries about the euro zone's debt crisis. 
 The Dow Jones industrial average  .DJI  gained 259.67 points, or 2.18 percent, to 12,153.46. The Standard & Poor's 500 Index  .SPX  gained 24.15 points, or 1.95 percent, to 1,263.84. The Nasdaq Composite Index  .IXIC  gained 53.60 points, or 2.04 percent, to 2,678.75.